# Component State And Inputs Repair

## Initializer Diagnostics

Messages:

```text
Property 'vm' has no initializer and is not definitely assigned in the constructor
Definite assignment assertions are not supported (arkts-no-definite-assignment)
```

Do not automatically change:

```ts
vm: AppViewModel
```

to:

```ts
vm!: AppViewModel
```

For UI that renders mutable VM fields, `vm!` silences initialization but does not define ArkUI state ownership and can leave runtime UI stale.

## Decision Table

| Child needs | Parent owns | Child declaration | Parent call |
|---|---|---|---|
| read immutable primitive/string | value | `@Prop title: string = ''` | `Child({ title: this.title })` |
| edit parent primitive | `@State query` | `@Link query: string` | `Child({ query: $query })` |
| observe shared object fields | `@State appState: AppState` where `AppState` is `@Observed` | `@ObjectLink state: AppState` | `Child({ state: this.appState })` |
| trigger behavior only | method/service | `onSave: () => void = () => {}` | `Child({ onSave: () => this.save() })` |
| service with no UI refresh | plain private service | `service: Service = new Service()` or constructor-owned | `Child({ service: this.service })` |

## Shared ViewModel Pattern

Prefer VM as command object and observed state as rendered data:

```ts
@Observed
class AppState {
  count: number = 0
}

class AppViewModel {
  readonly state: AppState = new AppState()

  increment(): void {
    this.state.count += 1
  }
}

@Entry
@Component
struct Index {
  private vm: AppViewModel = new AppViewModel()
  @State private appState: AppState = this.vm.state

  build() {
    Child({
      state: this.appState,
      onIncrement: () => this.vm.increment()
    })
  }
}

@Component
struct Child {
  @ObjectLink state: AppState
  onIncrement: () => void = () => {}

  build() {
    Button(`${this.state.count}`)
      .onClick(() => this.onIncrement())
  }
}
```

## If Keeping `@ObjectLink vm`

Only use when the VM class itself is intentionally an observed state object:

```ts
@Observed
class AppViewModel {
  currentStreak: number = 0
}

@Component
struct HomePage {
  @ObjectLink vm: AppViewModel
}
```

Do not use `$vm` with `@ObjectLink`; pass object reference:

```ts
HomePage({ vm: this.vm })
```

Use `$name` for `@Link` bindings, not for `@ObjectLink`.

## Warning Severity

Treat `arkts-no-definite-assignment` as high-risk when:

- prop name is `vm`, `viewModel`, `state`, `navStack`, or route params
- component reads mutable fields in `build()`
- button click mutates the same object
- runtime state propagation is required

It may be acceptable only for non-reactive injected services after confirming no rendered field depends on internal mutation.

